Commentary Text: Mujeeb to de Kock, out Caught by (sub)J Suchith!! That's a body blow for the Mumbai Indians - the well-set de Kock has been dismissed, backed away and that allowed Mujeeb to follow him, cramped up for room for the lofted on-drive, didn't get hold of the shot and all he managed was plenty of height. Commentary Text: Shankar to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught&Bowled!! Chipped back to the bowler! What a soft dismissal for Suryakumar Yadav. Instant revenge by Vijay Shankar. He's been so clever with his pace and hitting the right lengths. A huge blow for Mumbai as SKY is the man in form for them. Unfortunately, has to depart early here. Fuller and straighter, it stopped on the pitch which made Suryakumar check his drive too hard and uppishly to the right of the bowler. Shankar gets low in his followthrough and holds onto a smart catch. SRH will be delighted with this wicket. By the way, they also take the time-out. Suryakumar Yadav c and b Shankar 10(6) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Shankar to Rohit, out Caught by Virat Singh!! Lack of pace is the key here and local boy, Shankar knows the conditions better than anyone here. Just what the doctor ordered! The change of bowling bringing in a wicket for SRH and it's the big one of Rohit Sharma, who was looking in ominious touch. Cross-seam full delivery, Rohit had cleared his front leg and telegraphed his intentions quite early, slogs across the line but doesn't get anywhere off the middle. Skies it to deep mid-wicket where Virat Singh was setting himself under it and calmly takes his first catch. Yet again Hitman not converting his start.. Rohit c Virat Singh b Shankar 32(25) [4s-2 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Pollard to Virat Singh, out Warner Run Out!! Brilliance from Hardik! He had missed earlier to let Warner off but not this time. Virat dabbed this slower ball towards the point region and it was Warner's call for the single. Was quite risky and Hardik swoops in before firing a direct hit at the striker's end. The SRH skipper is way short and he started his walk back to the dugout as soon as the direct hit was made. Is this the turning point of the game? Warner run out (Hardik Pandya) 36(34) [4s-2 6s-2]
